segment_text: The Lord St. Simon marriage, and its curious termination, have long ceased to be a subject of interest in those exalted circles in which the unfortunate bridegroom moves.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Fresh scandals have eclipsed it, and their more piquant details have drawn the gossips away from this four-year-old drama.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: As I have reason to believe, however, that the full facts have never been revealed to the general public, and as my friend Sherlock Holmes had a considerable share in clearing the matter up, I feel that no memoir of him would be complete without some little sketch of this remarkable episode.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: It was a few weeks before my own marriage, during the days when I was still sharing rooms with Holmes in Baker Street, that he came home from an afternoon stroll to find a letter on the table waiting for him.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I had remained indoors all day, for the weather had taken a sudden turn to rain, with high autumnal winds, and the jezail bullet which I had brought back in one of my limbs as a relic of my Afghan campaign throbbed with dull persistence.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: With my body in one easy-chair and my legs upon another, I had surrounded myself with a cloud of newspapers until at last, saturated with the news of the day, I tossed them all aside and lay listless, watching the huge crest and monogram upon the envelope upon the table and wondering lazily who my friend’s noble correspondent could be.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Here is a very fashionable epistle,” I remarked as he entered.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Your morning letters, if I remember right, were from a fish-monger and a tide-waiter.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Yes, my correspondence has certainly the charm of variety,” he answered, smiling, “and the humbler are usually the more interesting.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: This looks like one of those unwelcome social summonses which call upon a man either to be bored or to lie.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: He broke the seal and glanced over the contents.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Oh, come, it may prove to be something of interest, after all.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Not social, then?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “No, distinctly professional.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “And from a noble client?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “One of the highest in England.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “My dear fellow, I congratulate you.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “I assure you, Watson, without affectation, that the status of my client is a matter of less moment to me than the interest of his case.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: It is just possible, however, that that also may not be wanting in this new investigation. You have been reading the papers diligently of late, have you not?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “It looks like it,” said I ruefully, pointing to a huge bundle in the corner. “I have had nothing else to do.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “It is fortunate, for you will perhaps be able to post me up. I read nothing except the criminal news and the agony column.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: The latter is always instructive. But if you have followed recent events so closely you must have read about Lord St. Simon and his wedding?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Oh, yes, with the deepest interest.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “That is well. The letter which I hold in my hand is from Lord St. Simon.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I will read it to you, and in return you must turn over these papers and let me have whatever bears upon the matter. This is what he says:
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “‘MY DEAR MR. SHERLOCK HOLMES,—Lord Backwater tells me that I may place implicit reliance upon your judgment and discretion.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I have determined, therefore, to call upon you and to consult you in reference to the very painful event which has occurred in connection with my wedding.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Mr. Lestrade, of Scotland Yard, is acting already in the matter, but he assures me that he sees no objection to your co-operation, and that he even thinks that it might be of some assistance.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I will call at four o’clock in the afternoon, and, should you have any other engagement at that time, I hope that you will postpone it, as this matter is of paramount importance. Yours faithfully, “‘ROBERT ST. SIMON.’
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “It is dated from Grosvenor Mansions, written with a quill pen, and the noble lord has had the misfortune to get a smear of ink upon the outer side of his right little finger,” remarked Holmes as he folded up the epistle.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “He says four o’clock. It is three now. He will be here in an hour.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Then I have just time, with your assistance, to get clear upon the subject. Turn over those papers and arrange the extracts in their order of time, while I take a glance as to who our client is.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: He picked a red-covered volume from a line of books of reference beside the mantelpiece.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Here he is,” said he, sitting down and flattening it out upon his knee. “‘Lord Robert Walsingham de Vere St. Simon, second son of the Duke of Balmoral.’ Hum!
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: ‘Arms: Azure, three caltrops in chief over a fess sable. Born in 1846.’ He’s forty-one years of age, which is mature for marriage.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Was Under-Secretary for the colonies in a late administration. The Duke, his father, was at one time Secretary for Foreign Affairs.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: They inherit Plantagenet blood by direct descent, and Tudor on the distaff side. Ha! Well, there is nothing very instructive in all this.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I think that I must turn to you Watson, for something more solid.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “I have very little difficulty in finding what I want,” said I, “for the facts are quite recent, and the matter struck me as remarkable.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I feared to refer them to you, however, as I knew that you had an inquiry on hand and that you disliked the intrusion of other matters.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Oh, you mean the little problem of the Grosvenor Square furniture van. That is quite cleared up now—though, indeed, it was obvious from the first.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Pray give me the results of your newspaper selections.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Here is the first notice which I can find. It is in the personal column of the _Morning Post_, and dates, as you see, some weeks back: ‘A marriage has been arranged,’ it says, ‘and will, if rumour is correct, very shortly take place, between Lord Robert St. Simon, second son of the Duke of Balmoral, and Miss Hatty Doran, the only daughter of Aloysius Doran. Esq., of San Francisco, Cal., U.S.A.’
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: That is all.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Terse and to the point,” remarked Holmes, stretching his long, thin legs towards the fire.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “There was a paragraph amplifying this in one of the society papers of the same week. Ah, here it is:
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: ‘There will soon be a call for protection in the marriage  market, for the present free-trade principle appears to tell heavily against our home product.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: One by one the management of the noble houses of Great Britain is passing into the hands of our fair cousins from across the Atlantic.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: An important addition has been made during the last week to the list of the prizes which have been borne away by these charming invaders.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Lord St. Simon, who has shown himself for over twenty years proof against the little god’s arrows, has now definitely announced his approaching marriage with Miss Hatty Doran, the fascinating daughter of a California millionaire.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Miss Doran, whose graceful figure and striking face attracted much attention at the Westbury House festivities, is an only child, and it is currently reported that her dowry will run to considerably over the six figures, with expectancies for the future.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: As it is an open secret that the Duke of Balmoral has been compelled to sell his pictures within the last few years, and as Lord St. Simon has no property of his own save the small estate of Birchmoor, it is obvious that the Californian heiress is not the only gainer by an alliance which will enable her to make the easy and common transition from a Republican lady to a British peeress.’”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Anything else?” asked Holmes, yawning.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Oh, yes; plenty. Then there is another note in the _Morning Post_ to say that the marriage would be an absolutely quiet one, that it would be at St. George’s, Hanover Square, that only half a dozen intimate friends would be invited, and that the party would return to the furnished house at Lancaster Gate which has been taken by Mr. Aloysius Doran.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Two days later—that is, on Wednesday last—there is a curt announcement that the wedding had taken place, and that the honeymoon would be passed at Lord Backwater’s place, near Petersfield.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Those are all the notices which appeared before the disappearance of the bride.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Before the what?” asked Holmes with a start.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “The vanishing of the lady.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “When did she vanish, then?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “At the wedding breakfast.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Indeed. This is more interesting than it promised to be; quite dramatic, in fact.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Yes; it struck me as being a little out of the common.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “They often vanish before the ceremony, and occasionally during the honeymoon; but I cannot call to mind anything quite so prompt as this. Pray let me have the details.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “I warn you that they are very incomplete.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Perhaps we may make them less so.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Such as they are, they are set forth in a single article of a morning paper of yesterday, which I will read to you. It is headed, ‘Singular Occurrence at a Fashionable Wedding’:
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “‘The family of Lord Robert St. Simon has been thrown into the greatest consternation by the strange and painful episodes which have taken place in connection with his wedding.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: The ceremony, as shortly announced in the papers of yesterday, occurred on the previous morning; but it is only now that it has been possible to confirm the strange rumours which have been so persistently floating about.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: In spite of the attempts of the friends to hush the matter up, so much public attention has now been drawn to it that no good purpose can be served by affecting to disregard what is a common subject for conversation.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “‘The ceremony, which was performed at St. George’s, Hanover Square, was a very quiet one, no one being present save the father of the bride, Mr. Aloysius Doran, the Duchess of Balmoral, Lord Backwater, Lord Eustace and Lady Clara St. Simon (the younger brother and sister of the bridegroom), and Lady Alicia Whittington.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: The whole party proceeded afterwards to the house of Mr. Aloysius Doran, at Lancaster Gate, where breakfast had been prepared.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: It appears that some little trouble was caused by a woman, whose name has not been ascertained, who endeavoured to force her way into the house after the bridal party, alleging that she had some claim upon Lord St. Simon.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: It was only after a painful and prolonged scene that she was ejected by the butler and the footman.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: The bride, who had fortunately entered the house before this unpleasant interruption, had sat down to breakfast with the rest, when she complained of a sudden indisposition and retired to her room.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Her prolonged absence having caused some comment, her father followed her, but learned from her maid that she had only come up to her chamber for an instant, caught up an ulster and bonnet, and hurried down to the passage.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: One of the footmen declared that he had seen a lady leave the house thus apparelled, but had refused to credit that it was his mistress, believing her to be with the company.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: On ascertaining that his daughter had disappeared, Mr. Aloysius Doran, in conjunction with the bridegroom, instantly put themselves in communication with the police, and very energetic inquiries are being made, which will probably result in a speedy clearing up of this very singular business.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Up to a late hour last night, however, nothing had transpired as to the whereabouts of the missing lady.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: There are rumours of foul play in the matter, and it is said that the police have caused the arrest of the woman who had caused the original disturbance, in the belief that, from jealousy or some other motive, she may have been concerned in the strange disappearance of the bride.’”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “And is that all?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Only one little item in another of the morning papers, but it is a suggestive one.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “And it is—”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “That Miss Flora Millar, the lady who had caused the disturbance, has actually been arrested. It appears that she was formerly a _danseuse_ at the Allegro, and that she has known the bridegroom for some years.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: There are no further particulars, and the whole case is in your hands now—so far as it has been set forth in the public press.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “And an exceedingly interesting case it appears to be. I would not have missed it for worlds.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: But there is a ring at the bell, Watson, and as the clock makes it a few minutes after four, I have no doubt that this will prove to be our noble client.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Do not dream of going, Watson, for I very much prefer having a witness, if only as a check to my own memory.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Lord Robert St. Simon,” announced our page-boy, throwing open the door.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: A gentleman entered, with a pleasant, cultured face, high-nosed and pale, with something perhaps of petulance about the mouth, and with the steady, well-opened eye of a man whose pleasant lot it had ever been to command and to be obeyed.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: His manner was brisk, and yet his general appearance gave an undue impression of age, for he had a slight forward stoop and a little bend of the knees as he walked.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: His hair, too, as he swept off his very curly-brimmed hat, was grizzled round the edges and thin upon the top.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: As to his dress, it was careful to the verge of foppishness, with high collar, black frock-coat, white waistcoat, yellow gloves, patent-leather shoes, and light-coloured gaiters.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: He advanced slowly into the room, turning his head from left to right, and swinging in his right hand the cord which held his golden eyeglasses.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Good-day, Lord St. Simon,” said Holmes, rising and bowing. “Pray take the basket-chair.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: This is my friend and colleague, Dr. Watson. Draw up a little to the fire, and we will talk this matter over.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “A most painful matter to me, as you can most readily imagine, Mr. Holmes. I have been cut to the quick.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I understand that you have already managed several delicate cases of this sort, sir, though I presume that they were hardly from the same class of society.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “No, I am descending.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “I beg pardon.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “My last client of the sort was a king.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Oh, really! I had no idea. And which king?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “The King of Scandinavia.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “What! Had he lost his wife?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “You can understand,” said Holmes suavely, “that I extend to the affairs of my other clients the same secrecy which I promise to you in yours.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Of course! Very right! very right! I’m sure I beg pardon. As to my own case, I am ready to give you any information which may assist you in forming an opinion.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Thank you. I have already learned all that is in the public prints, nothing more.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I presume that I may take it as correct—this article, for example, as to the disappearance of the bride.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Lord St. Simon glanced over it. “Yes, it is correct, as far as it goes.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “But it needs a great deal of supplementing before anyone could offer an opinion. I think that I may arrive at my facts most directly by questioning you.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Pray do so.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “When did you first meet Miss Hatty Doran?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “In San Francisco, a year ago.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “You were travelling in the States?” “Yes.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Did you become engaged then?” “No.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “But you were on a friendly footing?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “I was amused by her society, and she could see that I was amused.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Her father is very rich?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “He is said to be the richest man on the Pacific slope.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “And how did he make his money?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “In mining. He had nothing a few years ago. Then he struck gold, invested it, and came up by leaps and bounds.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Now, what is your own impression as to the young lady’s—your wife’s character?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: The nobleman swung his glasses a little faster and stared down into the fire.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “You see, Mr. Holmes,” said he, “my wife was twenty before her father became a rich man. During that time she ran free in a mining camp and wandered through woods or mountains, so that her education has come from Nature rather than from the schoolmaster.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: She is what we call in England a tomboy, with a strong nature, wild and free, unfettered by any sort of traditions. She is impetuous—volcanic, I was about to say.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: She is swift in making up her mind and fearless in carrying out her resolutions. On the other hand, I would not have given her the name which I have the honour to bear”—he gave a little stately cough—“had I not thought her to be at bottom a noble woman.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I believe that she is capable of heroic self-sacrifice and that anything dishonourable would be repugnant to her.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Have you her photograph?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “I brought this with me.” He opened a locket and showed us the full face of a very lovely woman.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: It was not a photograph but an ivory miniature, and the artist had brought out the full effect of the lustrous black hair, the large dark eyes, and the exquisite mouth.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Holmes gazed long and earnestly at it. Then he closed the locket and handed it back to Lord St. Simon.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “The young lady came to London, then, and you renewed your acquaintance?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Yes, her father brought her over for this last London season. I met her several times, became engaged to her, and have now married her.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “She brought, I understand, a considerable dowry?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “A fair dowry. Not more than is usual in my family.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “And this, of course, remains to you, since the marriage is a _fait accompli_?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “I really have made no inquiries on the subject.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Very naturally not. Did you see Miss Doran on the day before the wedding?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Yes.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Was she in good spirits?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Never better. She kept talking of what we should do in our future lives.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Indeed! That is very interesting. And on the morning of the wedding?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “She was as bright as possible—at least until after the ceremony.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “And did you observe any change in her then?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Well, to tell the truth, I saw then the first signs that I had ever seen that her temper was just a little sharp. The incident however, was too trivial to relate and can have no possible bearing upon the case.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Pray let us have it, for all that.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Oh, it is childish. She dropped her bouquet as we went towards the vestry. She was passing the front pew at the time, and it fell over into the pew.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: There was a moment’s delay, but the gentleman in the pew handed it up to her again, and it did not appear to be the worse for the fall.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Yet when I spoke to her of the matter, she answered me abruptly; and in the carriage, on our way home, she seemed absurdly agitated over this trifling cause.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Indeed! You say that there was a gentleman in the pew. Some of the general public were present, then?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Oh, yes. It is impossible to exclude them when the church is open.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “This gentleman was not one of your wife’s friends?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “No, no; I call him a gentleman by courtesy, but he was quite a common-looking person. I hardly noticed his appearance.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: But really I think that we are wandering rather far from the point.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Lady St. Simon, then, returned from the wedding in a less cheerful frame of mind than she had gone to it. What did she do on re-entering her father’s house?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “I saw her in conversation with her maid.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “And who is her maid?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Alice is her name. She is an American and came from California with her.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “A confidential servant?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “A little too much so. It seemed to me that her mistress allowed her to take great liberties. Still, of course, in America they look upon these things in a different way.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “How long did she speak to this Alice?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “I do not think Flora would hurt a fly.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Still, jealousy is a strange transformer of characters. Pray what is your own theory as to what took place?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Well, really, when I consider that she has turned her back—I will not say upon me, but upon so much that many have aspired to without success—I can hardly explain it in any other fashion.”

segment_text: “Well, certainly that is also a conceivable hypothesis,” said Holmes, smiling.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “By the same brilliant reasoning, every man’s body is to be found in the neighbourhood of his wardrobe. And pray what did you hope to arrive at through this?”

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Now my theory all along has been that Lady St. Simon was decoyed away by Flora Millar, and that she, with confederates, no doubt, was responsible for her disappearance. Here, signed with her initials, is the very note which was no doubt quietly slipped into her hand at the door and which lured her within their reach.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Very good, Lestrade,” said Holmes, laughing. “You really are very fine indeed. Let me see it.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: It was after five o’clock when Sherlock Holmes left me, but I had no time to be lonely, for within an hour there arrived a confectioner’s man with a very large flat box.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: This he unpacked with the help of a youth whom he had brought with him, and presently, to my very great astonishment, a quite epicurean little cold supper began to be laid out upon our humble lodging-house mahogany.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: There were a couple of brace of cold woodcock, a pheasant, a _pâté de foie gras_ pie with a group of ancient and cobwebby bottles.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “You seem to expect company. They have laid for five.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Yes, I fancy we may have some company dropping in,” said he. “I am surprised that Lord St. Simon has not already arrived.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: It was indeed our visitor of the afternoon who came bustling in, dangling his glasses more vigorously than ever, and with a very perturbed expression upon his aristocratic features.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “You must make allowance for this poor girl, placed in so unprecedented a position.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “If I may give an opinion,” remarked the strange gentleman, “we’ve had just a little too much secrecy over this business already. For my part, I should like all Europe and America to hear the rights of it.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: He was a small, wiry, sunburnt man, clean-shaven, with a sharp face and alert manner.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Then I’ll tell our story right away,” said the lady. “Frank here and I met in ’84, in McQuire’s camp, near the Rockies, where Pa was working a claim.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: We were engaged to each other, Frank and I; but then one day father struck a rich pocket and made a pile, while poor Frank here had a claim that petered out and came to nothing.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: The richer Pa grew the poorer was Frank; so at last Pa wouldn’t hear of our engagement lasting any longer, and he took me away to ’Frisco.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Frank wouldn’t throw up his hand, though; so he followed me there, and he saw me without Pa knowing anything about it. It would only have made him mad to know, so we just fixed it all up for ourselves.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Frank said that he would go and make his pile, too, and never come back to claim me until he had as much as Pa. So then I promised to wait for him to the end of time and pledged myself not to marry anyone else while he lived.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: ‘Why shouldn’t we be married right away, then,’ said he, ‘and then I will feel sure of you; and I won’t claim to be your husband until I come back?’
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Well, we talked it over, and he had fixed it all up so nicely, with a clergyman all ready in waiting, that we just did it right there; and then Frank went off to seek his fortune, and I went back to Pa.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “The next I heard of Frank was that he was in Montana, and then he went prospecting in Arizona, and then I heard of him from New Mexico. After that came a long newspaper story about how a miners’ camp had been attacked by Apache Indians, and there was my Frank’s name among the killed.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I fainted dead away, and I was very sick for months after. Pa thought I had a decline and took me to half the doctors in ’Frisco.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Not a word of news came for a year and more, so that I never doubted that Frank was really dead. Then Lord St. Simon came to ’Frisco, and we came to London, and a marriage was arranged, and Pa was very pleased, but I felt all the time that no man on this earth would ever take the place in my heart that had been given to my poor Frank.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Still, if I had married Lord St. Simon, of course I’d have done my duty by him. We can’t command our love, but we can our actions.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I went to the altar with him with the intention to make him just as good a wife as it was in me to be. But you may imagine what I felt when, just as I came to the altar rails, I glanced back and saw Frank standing and looking at me out of the first pew.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I thought it was his ghost at first; but when I looked again there he was still, with a kind of question in his eyes, as if to ask me whether I were glad or sorry to see him. I wonder I didn’t drop.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I know that everything was turning round, and the words of the clergyman were just like the buzz of a bee in my ear. I didn’t know what to do.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Should I stop the service and make a scene in the church? I glanced at him again, and he seemed to know what I was thinking, for he raised his finger to his lips to tell me to be still.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Then I saw him scribble on a piece of paper, and I knew that he was writing me a note. As I passed his pew on the way out I dropped my bouquet over to him, and he slipped the note into my hand when he returned me the flowers.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: It was only a line asking me to join him when he made the sign to me to do so. Of course I never doubted for a moment that my first duty was now to him, and I determined to do just whatever he might direct.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “When I got back I told my maid, who had known him in California, and had always been his friend. I ordered her to say nothing, but to get a few things packed and my ulster ready.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I know I ought to have spoken to Lord St. Simon, but it was dreadful hard before his mother and all those great people. I just made up my mind to run away and explain afterwards.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I hadn’t been at the table ten minutes before I saw Frank out of the window at the other side of the road. He beckoned to me and then began walking into the Park.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I slipped out, put on my things, and followed him. Some woman came talking something or other about Lord St. Simon to me—seemed to me from the little I heard as if he had a little secret of his own before marriage also—but I managed to get away from her and soon overtook Frank.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: We got into a cab together, and away we drove to some lodgings he had taken in Gordon Square, and that was my true wedding after all those years of waiting.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Frank had been a prisoner among the Apaches, had escaped, came on to ’Frisco, found that I had given him up for dead and had gone to England, followed me there, and had come upon me at last on the very morning of my second wedding.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “I saw it in a paper,” explained the American. “It gave the name and the church but not where the lady lived.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Then we had a talk as to what we should do, and Frank was all for openness, but I was so ashamed of it all that I felt as if I should like to vanish away and never see any of them again—just sending a line to Pa, perhaps, to show him that I was alive.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: It was awful to me to think of all those lords and ladies sitting round that breakfast-table and waiting for me to come back. So Frank took my wedding-clothes and things and made a bundle of them, so that I should not be traced, and dropped them away somewhere where no one could find them.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: It is likely that we should have gone on to Paris to-morrow, only that this good gentleman, Mr. Holmes, came round to us this evening, though how he found us is more than I can think, and he showed us very clearly and kindly that I was wrong and that Frank was right, and that we should be putting ourselves in the wrong if we were so secret.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Then he offered to give us a chance of talking to Lord St. Simon alone, and so we came right away round to his rooms at once. Now, Robert, you have heard it all, and I am very sorry if I have given you pain, and I hope that you do not think very meanly of me.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Lord St. Simon had by no means relaxed his rigid attitude, but had listened with a frowning brow and a compressed lip to this long narrative.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Excuse me,” he said, “but it is not my custom to discuss my most intimate personal affairs in this public manner.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Then you won’t forgive me? You won’t shake hands before I go?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Oh, certainly, if it would give you any pleasure.” He put out his hand and coldly grasped that which she extended to him.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “I had hoped,” suggested Holmes, “that you would have joined us in a friendly supper.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “I think that there you ask a little too much,” responded his Lordship. “I may be forced to acquiesce in these recent developments, but I can hardly be expected to make merry over them.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I think that with your permission I will now wish you all a very good-night.” He included us all in a sweeping bow and stalked out of the room.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Then I trust that you at least will honour me with your company,” said Sherlock Holmes.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “It is always a joy to meet an American, Mr. Moulton, for I am one of those who believe that the folly of a monarch and the blundering of a minister in far-gone years will not prevent our children from being some day citizens of the same world-wide country under a flag which shall be a quartering of the Union Jack with the Stars and Stripes.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “The case has been an interesting one,” remarked Holmes when our visitors had left us, “because it serves to show very clearly how simple the explanation may be of an affair which at first sight seems to be almost inexplicable.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Nothing could be more natural than the sequence of events as narrated by this lady, and nothing stranger than the result when viewed, for instance, by Mr. Lestrade of Scotland Yard.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “You were not yourself at fault at all, then?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “From the first, two facts were very obvious to me, the one that the lady had been quite willing to undergo the wedding ceremony, the other that she had repented of it within a few minutes of returning home.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: Obviously something had occurred during the morning, then, to cause her to change her mind. What could that something be?
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: She could not have spoken to anyone when she was out, for she had been in the company of the bridegroom. Had she seen someone, then?
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: If she had, it must be someone from America because she had spent so short a time in this country that she could hardly have allowed anyone to acquire so deep an influence over her that the mere sight of him would induce her to change her plans so completely.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: You see we have already arrived, by a process of exclusion, at the idea that she might have seen an American. Then who could this American be, and why should he possess so much influence over her?
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: It might be a lover; it might be a husband. Her young womanhood had, I knew, been spent in rough scenes and under strange conditions.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: So far I had got before I ever heard Lord St. Simon’s narrative. When he told us of a man in a pew, of the change in the bride’s manner, of so transparent a device for obtaining a note as the dropping of a bouquet, of her resort to her confidential maid, and of her very significant allusion to claim-jumping—which in miners’ parlance means taking possession of that which another person has a prior claim to—the whole situation became absolutely clear.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: She had gone off with a man, and the man was either a lover or was a previous husband—the chances being in favour of the latter.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “And how in the world did you find them?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “It might have been difficult, but friend Lestrade held information in his hands the value of which he did not himself know. The initials were, of course, of the highest importance, but more valuable still was it to know that within a week he had settled his bill at one of the most select London hotels.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “How did you deduce the select?”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “By the select prices. Eight shillings for a bed and eightpence for a glass of sherry pointed to one of the most expensive hotels.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: There are not many in London which charge at that rate. In the second one which I visited in Northumberland Avenue, I learned by an inspection of the book that Francis H. Moulton, an American gentleman, had left only the day before, and on looking over the entries against him, I came upon the very items which I had seen in the duplicate bill.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: His letters were to be forwarded to 226 Gordon Square; so thither I travelled, and being fortunate enough to find the loving couple at home, I ventured to give them some paternal advice and to point out to them that it would be better in every way that they should make their position a little clearer both to the general public and to Lord St. Simon in particular.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I invited them to meet him here, and, as you see, I made him keep the appointment.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “But with no very good result,” I remarked. “His conduct was certainly not very gracious.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: “Ah, Watson,” said Holmes, smiling, “perhaps you would not be very gracious either, if, after all the trouble of wooing and wedding, you found yourself deprived in an instant of wife and of fortune.
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain

segment_text: I think that we may judge Lord St. Simon very mercifully and thank our stars that we are never likely to find ourselves in the same position. Draw your chair up and hand me my violin, for the only problem we have still to solve is how to while away these bleak autumnal evenings.”
scene_description: indoors, Victorian sitting room, fireplace, autumnal rain
